ontent\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Excellent! Now I've found the core issue. Let me create a comprehensive analysis document:\\n\\n## Shadow Branch Cleanup Bug Analysis\\n\\nBased on thorough code review of the manual commit strategy files, I've identified the shadow branch cleanup bug:\\n\\n### Bug Summary\\n\\nAfter the second commit in a test (either same session with two commits, or two separate sessions each with one commit), the shadow branch is **NOT being deleted**, even though it should be.\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n\\nThe bug is in **`PostCommit()` in `manual_commit_hooks.go`**, specifically in how shadow branches are tracked for deletion:\\n\\n**Lines 657-658 initialize the deletion map:**\\n```go\\nshadowBranchesToDelete := make(map[string]struct{})\\n```\\n\\n**Lines 665-774 iterate through sessions:**\\n- For each session, `TransitionAndLog()` is called with a handler (line 730)\\n- The handler may trigger `HandleCondense()` or `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched()` (line 504, 523)\\n- These handlers call `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` (line 505, 524)\\n- **Only if `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` returns `true`**, the code calls:\\n  ```go\\n  h.condensed = h.s.condenseAndUpdateState(...)  // line 516, 536\\n  ```\\n- Inside `condenseAndUpdateState()` (line 823), the shadow branch is added to the deletion map:\\n  ```go\\n  shadowBranchesToDelete[shadowBranchName] = struct{}{}  // line 823\\n  ```\\n\\n**Lines 778-794 perform the actual deletion:**\\n```go\\nfor shadowBranchName := range shadowBranchesToDelete {\\n    if uncondensedActiveOnBranch[shadowBranchName] {\\n        // ... skip\\n    }\\n    if err := deleteShadowBranch(repo, shadowBranchName) {\\n        // ... log error\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### The Problem\\n\\n**Shadow branches are only marked for deletion if condensation succeeds.** If a session doesn't meet the condensation criteria (specifically `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` returns `false`), **the branch is never added to `shadowBranchesToDelete`, so it never gets deleted later**.\\n\\nThis happens when:\\n1. A second session starts on a new base commit (different commit hash)\\n2. Both sessions get separate shadow branches\\n3. When the first session commits, `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` succeeds and condensation happens\\n4. When the second session commits, if `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` returns `false` (e.g., file overlap check fails), **the second session's branch is never added to `shadowBranchesToDelete`**\\n5. The loop at line 778 never deletes it\\n\\n### Why `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` Might Return False\\n\\nLooking at `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` (lines 560-582):\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (h *postCommitActionHandler) shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck(isActive bool) bool {\\n    if !h.hasNew {\\n        return false  // No new content\\n    }\\n    if len(h.filesTouchedBefore) == 0 {\\n        return isActive  // ACTIVE: yes; IDLE/ENDED: no\\n    }\\n    // Check if committed files overlap with session files\\n    var committedTouchedFiles []string\\n    for _, f := range h.filesTouchedBefore {\\n        if _, ok := h.committedFileSet[f]; ok {\\n            committedTouchedFiles = append(committedTouchedFiles, f)\\n        }\\n    }\\n    if len(committedTouchedFiles) == 0 {\\n        return false  // No file overlap\\n    }\\n    return filesOverlapWithContent(...)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nIn a test scenario:\\n- If the second session modifies **different files** than what was committed (the files from the first session's commit)\\n- Or if `hasNew` is determined to be `false` for IDLE/ENDED sessions\\n- Then `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck()` returns `false`\\n- And the shadow branch is never added to `shadowBranchesToDelete`\\n\\n### The Fix Needed\\n\\n**Shadow branches should be marked for deletion REGARDLESS of whether condensation succeeds.**\\n\\nThe fix should be in one of two places:\\n\\n**Option A:** In `HandleCondense()` and `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched()` - a